# John Edward Duncan

John Edward Duncan (1884â€“1959) was a member of the New Zealand Legislative Council from 22 September 1937 to 21 September 1944; then 22 September 1944 to 31 December 1950 when the Council was abolished. He was appointed by the First Labour Government.
He was from Auckland then Wharepuhunga.
